{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3ecccc8a-0d78-40ef-b0ae-467d03e4c017","content":"For a .NET Web API project, use the `webapi` template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi -n MyApi\n```\n\n**Authentication options** (via `--auth`):\n\n| Option | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single-tenant Azure AD (org accounts) |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows/Negotiate authentication |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```bash\n# Azure AD single-org auth\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain contoso.onmicrosoft.com\n\n# Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C\n```\n\nYou can also add JWT Bearer auth manually via `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` if you need a custom identity provider. Run `dotnet new webapi --help` for all options.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1a9f53f1-ce7c-427c-a49c-cfdb65c7c711","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This is a general knowledge question about .NET (likely, given the repository context with dotnet plugins). I can answer this from my knowledge without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":304,"requestId":"A80C:1BE3:CA69FD:E514C7:6A02798B"},"id":"b11fef8b-fe83-46bb-a89f-3bc849148d4b","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:51:30.395Z","parentId":"8fb9e779-5bdd-4cf5-9bc8-fa3595f36c68"}
